<div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-third">
<div style="background-color:#000000; color:#FFFFFF; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; font-family: PT Mono;">
===<center><span style="font-family: PT Mono">'''Lvl_351.mp4 - 7/12/████ - BEGIN LOG'''</span></center>===
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
Operative Landon Miller, a [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F]] operative, was investigating the sudden disappearance of a large forest in Russia, based on reports from wanderers who allegedly "escaped the level."
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

Landon: "How would that relate to the missing forest?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Wanderer: "Well, I was in the forest, lost, then fell through the floor. I woke up again in the forest, but it looked all real."</div>
<br>
Landon: "How would you even know if you were in the Backrooms? How would you even know about levels?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Wanderer: "I heard rumors on the internet. A bunch of geeks obsessed with the concept of liminal spaces. It talks about levels and some other shit."</div>
<br>
Sargent Jaylen: "Landon, maybe he's not bullshitting. What if this is actually real?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Landon: "Who knows? This guy might be insane."</div>
<br>
<center>[CALL ENDED]</center>
<br>
[Several days later]

Landon and operatives arrive on [[Level 200]], equipped with shotguns and M4 Carbines.

Operative 1: "Hey, that house looks out of place. We've never seen that before. Let's go check it out."
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Operative 2: "Yeah, let's see what's inside."</div>
<br>
[The operatives enter the house and find nothing.]
<br>
Operative 1: "Well, that was a bust. Let's move on."
<br>
[They exit the house and are suddenly in a new environment. A green and lush forest.]

Landon: "Hey, where are we?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Operative 2: "A new level?"</div>
<br>
[They explore the new level, which seems safe at first.]
<br>
Operative 1: "Man, maybe the Backrooms gods should spice up their game. We've got a dozen of these forest levels."
<br>
[Suddenly, an operative is attacked by a zombie-like creature.]

Operative: "SHOOT THIS THING! GET OFF ME! HELP ME!"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">[Gunfire echoes as the creature is neutralized.]</div>
<br>
[The group continues exploring and finds another house. Inside, they meet an old woman.]

Landon: "Hello, madam?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">Old Woman: "Вы, шуты. Ты будешь страдать под моим гневом."</div>
<br>
[[File:Baba Yaga .png|center|thumb|500x500px]]
[Zombies emerge from the house, surrounding the operatives. The operatives open fire and kill the zombies. They then shoot the old woman.]

Operative: "Batshit bitch."
<br>
[The old woman bleeds out, appearing dead.]

[Just as they attempt to leave the house, blood splatters everywhere.]

Landon: "What the hell?"
<br>
<div style="text-align: right;">[Baba Yaga, the old woman, rises again, her claws cutting through the air.]</div>
<br>
[The operatives are attacked. One is swiftly killed and swallowed whole by Baba Yaga.]

Operative 2: "AAAAAH!"
<br>
[The remaining operatives fire their weapons at Baba Yaga, but she remains unphased.]

Landon: "We need to get out of here!"
<br>
[The operatives run as Baba Yaga chases them, jumping incredible distances.]

Landon: "Shit!"
<br>
[During his escape, Landon trips and falls.]

Landon: "No—!"
<br>
[In desperation, Landon throws a rock at Baba Yaga's face, stunning her for a moment, allowing him to escape.]

Landon: "What the hell...?!"
<br>
[As he runs, Landon no-clips, transporting him to [[Level 10]].]

<center>[CALL ENDED]</center>

[End Log]

